adventure
========

Short description.

Usage
-----

::

    adventure [--help|-h] [--version]

Where::

    --help|-h           Show this help message and exit.
    --version           Show version number and exit.

Long description.

Dependencies
------------

Tested on OSX, ought to work on others.
Python 2.7.

For dependencies see requirements.txt

Install
-------

::

    pip install adventure

Known Problems
--------------

Thanks
------

Hacking
-------

Create a virtualenv in Python 2.7::

    mkvitualenv -p python2.7 adventure

On OSX, Pyglet won't 'pip install' for me, so get source from the Hg repo::

    hg clone https://code.google.com/p/pyglet/
    cd pyglet
    python setup.py install

Install all other runtime requirements::

    pip install -r requirements.txt

Install the requirements needed to develop, e.g. to run tests::

    pip install -r requirements-dev.txt

Generate an executable script on the PATH which calls my 'main' function (as
specified in my setup.py's 'entry_points' config) and make sure that imports
find my local source before any installed packages of the same name.::

    python setup.py develop

Run tests::

    make test

Run the program::

    adventure

See the Makefile for other handy targets.


